  "min_face_size_guide": "Min Face Size Guide",
  "min_face_size_guide_content": "<strong>Face Recognition Minimum Size</strong>\n\nThis feature helps you understand the minimum face size required for accurate facial recognition in the camera view.\n\n<strong>How it works:</strong>\n• Click \"Visualize\" to show face detection areas on the camera view\n• The displayed icons represent the minimum size a face must be for reliable recognition\n• Faces smaller than this size may not be detected consistently\n\n<strong>Guidelines:</strong>\n• <strong>Larger minimum size:</strong> More accurate detection, fewer false positives\n• <strong>Smaller minimum size:</strong> Detects distant faces, but may increase false detections\n• Position the minimum size icons to match your monitoring requirements\n\n<strong>Best Practice:</strong>\nAdjust the minimum face size based on the distance between the camera and the area you want to monitor for optimal recognition accuracy.",
  "min_face_size_guide_title": "Min Face Size Guide",
  "min_face_size_help_message": "<strong>What is Min Face Size?</strong>\n\nThe minimum pixel size required for face recognition.\n\n<strong>Recommended Settings:</strong>\n• <strong>50px:</strong> Standard distance detection (recommended)\n• <strong>30px:</strong> Long distance detection\n• <strong>70px:</strong> Close range high-precision detection\n\n<strong>Notes:</strong>\n• Smaller values may increase false positives\n• Larger values may reduce recognition rate\n• Adjust according to camera resolution",
